on inside the Covelli Center in Columbus on Saturday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg"><media:title>2026 Rifle NCAA National Champions</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:39:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>8</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58864</s:story_id></item><item><title>Michael Continues to Lead WVU at The Hootie</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/23/golf-michael-continues-to-lead-wvu-at-the-hootie</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/23/golf-michael-continues-to-lead-wvu-at-the-hootie</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Bulls Bay" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2021/3/26/BullsBay_00025.JPG" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University freshman Jack Michael shot 2-under-par on Monday and is in ninth place after 36 holes at The Hootie at Bulls Bay in Awendaw, South Carolina.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2021/3/26/BullsBay_00025.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2021/3/26/BullsBay_00025.JPG"><media:title>Bulls Bay</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2021/3/26/BullsBay_00025.JPG" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubD